 We see that, generally, spouses communicate well.
 About two in three men indicate that they would tell their wife if they
 do not agree with something.
 This is not too different for female co-heads.
 Based on these two variables, we also construct a new dummy variable that
 is one if both spouses indicate that they would always or mostly tell each
 other if they do not agree.
 In the entire sample, we find that out of 2,544 households, about 1,435
