\begin_layout Standard
As a follow up questions, we also asked what happens when one spouse tells
 the other that he or she does not agree.
 Here, we focus on instances where spouses indicate that they discuss and
 come to a solution that is mutually agreed upon.
 We find that in the entire sample, 66 percent of male co-heads agree in
 that spouses talk and come to a solution.
 Again, we find little difference between men and women: 65 percent of women
 indicate that a mutually beneficial solution is sought.
 In half of all households in our sample, there is agreement between spouses
 that a mutually agreed upon solution is discussed.
