 We do not find that the intervention increases the likelihood that male
 co-heads tell the female co-heads if they disagree (column 2, row 1).
 We also do not find a significant impact on the likelihood that the female
 co-head tells the male co-head if she disagrees (column 4, row 1).
 We also do not find that the intervention increases two way communication
 (column 6, row 1).
 We do, however, find that the intervention increases the likelihood that
 man indicate that a mutual agreement is sought when there is disagreement
 (column 2, row 3).
